00:10:55.000 --> 00:11:00.000
So we start out with some kind of video input, right?

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:08.000
We have a person talking into the camera, and we run that through a program called FFmpeg.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:18.000
And that will split up the movie into a speech track, just the audio, and a bunch of JPEGs for the video.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:27.000
That's necessary because the only thing that today's GPT API understands is textual prompts and images.

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:30.000
Those are the only kinds of inputs that you can give it.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:33.000
And the only kinds of outputs it can give you are text.

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:36.000
Well, it can also make function calls, but mostly text.

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:42.000
