00:24:47.000 --> 00:24:57.000
Streamlet is by far the best known Python web application framework for data scientists.

00:24:57.000 --> 00:25:07.000
That being said, I think the reason for Streamlet's popularity is extreme ease of getting started.

00:25:07.000 --> 00:25:11.000
And I think one of the things that differentiates Shiny from Streamlet,

00:25:11.000 --> 00:25:16.000
probably the main thing, is that it is almost as easy to get started with,

00:25:16.000 --> 00:25:19.000
but it is much more powerful and flexible.

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:23.000
So if you know anyone who's built a lot of Streamlet apps,

00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:24.000
you can ask them.

00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:30.000
They'll probably tell you that at a certain point, you kind of need to do something else.

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:35.000
The main reason is because every time you do anything in a Streamlet app,

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:38.000
it re-executes your entire Streamlet app from top to bottom.

00:25:39.000 --> 00:25:41.000
And for simple apps, that's fine.

00:25:41.000 --> 00:25:46.000
